    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="382"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/736</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Halifax</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency the British
                    Ambassador and has the honor, with reference to <hi rend="italic"
                        >Aide-Mémoire</hi> 131/8/44 of January 31, 1944, to inform the Ambassador
                    that the American Chargé d’Affaires at Tehran has been instructed by telegraph
                    to lend his support, in concert with his British and Soviet colleagues and the
                    military authorities, in effecting the early conclusion of the railway
                    agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-10">February 10,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
